==Old English==

===Etymology===
Germanic ''tīra-'', from Indo-European ''*dei-''.

Cognate with Old Norse [[tírr]] ‘glory, renown’.  A Germanic variant, ''*tērīn-'', gave Old High German ''zierī'' (German [[Zier]] ‘splendour, beauty’).

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /ti:ɹ/

===Noun===
'''tīr''' ''m''
# [[fame]], [[glory]]

